This paper is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with biomedical image segmentation using neural networks. The use of adversarial networks for domain adaptation also suggests that it could belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The mention of digitization techniques and image datasets suggests that it could also belong to the Multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category. Finally, the use of neural networks and deep learning techniques suggests that it could belong to the Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) sub-category.
